Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.98,0:00:11.32,Main,,0,0,0,,I put on the armillary compass\NI found in the laboratory basement,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.32,0:00:15.66,Main,,0,0,0,,which sent me back to\N19th century London with Mari.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.12,0:00:19.08,Main,,0,0,0,,You've got to be kidding me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.08,0:00:22.50,Main,,0,0,0,,This is the worst possible time,\Nwhen I'm still fighting with Futa!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.37,0:00:26.88,Main,,0,0,0,,There, we met the scientist, Mr. Faraday.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.88,0:00:32.84,Main,,0,0,0,,And then he used his electromagnetic...\Num... rotation device...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.84,0:00:37.55,Main,,0,0,0,,for an experiment that proved a relationship\Nbetween electricity and magnetism.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.55,0:00:43.52,Main,,0,0,0,,But Mr. Farraday's patron, Sir Davy,\Nsaid this about his results...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.56,0:00:49.32,Main,,0,0,0,,These experimental results and your thesis\Nare both stolen from our research!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.32,0:00:51.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Wait, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.40,0:00:54.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Things were looking real bad, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.20,0:00:55.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.08,0:01:01.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Something happened, so I couldn't\Neven worry about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.79,0:01:02.83,Main,,0,0,0,,Where's Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.38,0:02:39.93,Main,,0,0,0,,"Episode 6\NFaraday's Resolve"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.13,0:02:43.18,Main,,0,0,0,,No... I don't like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.18,0:02:47.93,Main,,0,0,0,,I can't go home... I can't go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.93,0:02:52.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Go on, drink this. It'll warm you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.48,0:02:56.69,Main,,0,0,0,,As I understand it, when Mari\Nwould go back into the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.69,0:03:01.74,Main,,0,0,0,,she would return naturally after a\Ncertain amount of time had passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.74,0:03:07.04,Main,,0,0,0,,You came here this time\Nunder the same circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.04,0:03:12.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Yet Mari returned to her own time\Nwithout you. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.42,0:03:17.76,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.88,0:03:22.05,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, it's okay. When a\Nscientific experiment fails,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.05,0:03:25.05,Main,,0,0,0,,or presents a phenomenon\Nyou've never seen before,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.05,0:03:27.14,Main,,0,0,0,,there's always a reason for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.14,0:03:28.81,Main,,0,0,0,,If we can figure out a reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.81,0:03:29.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.94,0:03:36.19,Main,,0,0,0,,What would you understand?\NScience is all you talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.19,0:03:41.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Look at the situation\Nyour "science" has put me in!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.49,0:03:46.49,Main,,0,0,0,,I can't take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.49,0:03:49.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Let me go home! Send me home!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.33,0:03:50.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka! Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.87,0:03:54.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Let me go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.01,0:04:05.59,Main,,0,0,0,,It's no use. I can't find a single clue\Nabout how to bring Waka back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.59,0:04:08.18,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun! Awful news!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.18,0:04:09.18,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.39,0:04:12.48,Main,,0,0,0,,She's panicking...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.31,0:04:14.94,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.94,0:04:16.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.69,0:04:21.24,Main,,0,0,0,,I... I left Waka behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.24,0:04:25.41,Main,,0,0,0,,If I had only told her the way to get back...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.41,0:04:28.08,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sure we'll find a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.03,0:04:30.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.66,0:04:34.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Breach of contract? My husband?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.37,0:04:37.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes. I can't tell you all the details,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.58,0:04:40.13,Main,,0,0,0,,but Dr. Hayase may have\Ncommitted a severe breach
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.13,0:04:43.84,Main,,0,0,0,,of the contract he signed with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.34,0:04:48.05,Main,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I want his laboratory opened
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.05,0:04:53.35,Main,,0,0,0,,and a full delivery of all\Nhis research materials to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.35,0:04:55.52,Main,,0,0,0,,His research materials?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.52,0:04:58.36,Main,,0,0,0,,What kind of contract did he sign?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.36,0:05:01.23,Main,,0,0,0,,There's no need for you to know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.23,0:05:04.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Just be quiet and comply with our request.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.99,0:05:08.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Request? This sounds more like a threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.82,0:05:12.04,Main,,0,0,0,,We don't mind taking this to the authorities.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.04,0:05:14.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Take it anywhere you want!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.33,0:05:15.54,Main,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.29,0:05:21.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Then I'll be able to have a good look at the\Ncontract. I'll go through the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.09,0:05:22.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, please leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.63,0:05:27.93,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm losing all my customers because of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.93,0:05:29.80,Main,,0,0,0,,This is obstruction of my business.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.68,0:05:33.43,Main,,0,0,0,,I apologize. We'll return later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.43,0:05:36.94,Main,,0,0,0,,As apology for sending your customers away,\NI'll buy a few things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.81,0:05:39.86,Main,,0,0,0,,From here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.86,0:05:41.27,Main,,0,0,0,,...to here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.69,0:05:45.78,Main,,0,0,0,,No, thank you! I don't accept\Nsuch random purchases!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.78,0:05:49.78,Main,,0,0,0,,I work hard to make those\Nfor people who love cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.78,0:05:53.58,Main,,0,0,0,,The layering in these mille-feuilles\Nwas done with great care.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.58,0:05:56.79,Main,,0,0,0,,I can tell just from looking\Nhow much time it took you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.87,0:05:59.83,Main,,0,0,0,,This gâteau chocolat
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.83,0:06:05.05,Main,,0,0,0,,has a hint of chocolat mon amour\Nfrom Dolce de Michelle in France, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.05,0:06:06.84,Main,,0,0,0,,They're very good cakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.05,0:06:10.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your patronage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.30,0:06:16.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mikage... Are you sure about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.48,0:06:19.48,Main,,0,0,0,,She's a smart person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.70,0:06:35.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.16,0:06:37.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Good morning! Have a good sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.96,0:06:40.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Um... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.54,0:06:44.25,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to make a lady\Nsleep on the sofa,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.25,0:06:46.13,Main,,0,0,0,,but it was all I had.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.13,0:06:47.42,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.42,0:06:51.51,Main,,0,0,0,,I got tired from all the crying\Nand fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.51,0:06:54.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Hold on. I can make breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.26,0:06:55.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.51,0:06:59.10,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry about yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.98,0:07:05.19,Main,,0,0,0,,I... well... I took my anger out on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.19,0:07:07.11,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't sweat it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.11,0:07:08.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Go on, wash up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.24,0:07:17.83,Main,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just a nightmare...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.83,0:07:19.83,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka! It's done!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.79,0:07:23.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Wow! It looks delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.09,0:07:30.01,Main,,0,0,0,,You haven't eaten since yesterday!\NIt's only natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.01,0:07:30.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Go on!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.63,0:07:32.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Th-Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.09,0:07:36.51,Main,,0,0,0,,First, eat a good meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.51,0:07:38.93,Main,,0,0,0,,You can worry about the rest after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.73,0:07:42.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Sure... Let's eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.06,0:07:45.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.56,0:07:46.69,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.69,0:07:49.61,Main,,0,0,0,,I believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.61,0:07:52.07,Main,,0,0,0,,My brother's still back in my time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.07,0:07:53.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Your brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.24,0:07:54.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.24,0:07:57.45,Main,,0,0,0,,He's really smart and reliable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.45,0:08:00.29,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, too. She can be a scatterbrain,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.29,0:08:03.08,Main,,0,0,0,,but she really comes through when it counts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.08,0:08:05.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I trust them both.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.75,0:08:08.30,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sure they'll find a way to help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.76,0:08:12.42,Main,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.47,0:08:20.31,Main,,0,0,0,,I wonder how long it's been there...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.31,0:08:23.35,Main,,0,0,0,,I guess there's no way to get Waka back...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.35,0:08:26.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka must be feeling so lonely...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.23,0:08:30.03,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.03,0:08:32.53,Main,,0,0,0,,I remember! Papa told me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.53,0:08:34.45,Main,,0,0,0,,And when you get back,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.45,0:08:39.45,Main,,0,0,0,,tell Shun to press the triangle button\Nin the middle of the keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.45,0:08:41.04,Main,,0,0,0,,The triangle button?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.04,0:08:45.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah! He said it would\Nteach you the system controls!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.50,0:08:49.25,Main,,0,0,0,,In the center?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.25,0:08:50.34,Main,,0,0,0,,This one?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.34,0:08:52.71,Main,,0,0,0,,Probably!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.71,0:08:54.93,Main,,0,0,0,,I was being careful not to touch things
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.93,0:08:59.22,Main,,0,0,0,,when someone was in the past,\Nso as not to cause any trouble, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.52,0:09:11.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Would you like more tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.57,0:09:13.57,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.99,0:09:19.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Faraday! Awful news!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.07,0:09:20.37,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.37,0:09:23.95,Main,,0,0,0,,Sir Davy's been going around\Neverywhere since last night,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.95,0:09:27.42,Main,,0,0,0,,telling everyone you stole\Nhis and Dr. Wollaston's research!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.42,0:09:28.96,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.96,0:09:33.42,Main,,0,0,0,,I guess he didn't like that his apprentice\Ngot results when he didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.42,0:09:37.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Of course, we don't believe\Nyou'd do something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.26,0:09:41.01,Main,,0,0,0,,But it's been the talk of\Nthe society all morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.01,0:09:45.43,Main,,0,0,0,,It's just a rumor... but it's possible\Nhe may oppose your membership
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.43,0:09:47.27,Main,,0,0,0,,in the Royal Institution.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.27,0:09:51.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Sir Davy has a lot of influence\Nwith the Institution.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.40,0:09:55.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah... And some people might use this\Nto curry favor with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.94,0:09:57.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.20,0:10:07.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Wait, please! Sir Davy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.91,0:10:12.09,Main,,0,0,0,,I swear, I didn't steal your research!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.09,0:10:14.80,Main,,0,0,0,,I got those results from my own experiment!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.80,0:10:18.30,Main,,0,0,0,,I will firmly denounce you
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.30,0:10:21.26,Main,,0,0,0,,as a shameless fraud\Nwho stole his patron's research.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.26,0:10:22.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.85,0:10:28.06,Main,,0,0,0,,At this rate, you may be left unable to\Ntake part in scientific study anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.77,0:10:38.28,Main,,0,0,0,,He wants to take science away from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.28,0:10:40.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.67,0:10:58.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.26,0:11:02.97,Main,,0,0,0,,Please, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.89,0:11:10.64,Main,,0,0,0,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.64,0:11:12.44,Main,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.44,0:11:15.69,Main,,0,0,0,,You were Faraday's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.69,0:11:17.32,Main,,0,0,0,,His friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.44,0:11:23.74,Main,,0,0,0,,Please! Don't take science from him!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.74,0:11:27.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Did you come running after me to say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.33,0:11:28.95,Main,,0,0,0,,Pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.95,0:11:32.29,Main,,0,0,0,,He really does love science!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.29,0:11:37.17,Main,,0,0,0,,To take that from him... It's going too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.17,0:11:39.01,Main,,0,0,0,,He's getting what's coming to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.17,0:11:43.01,Main,,0,0,0,,You're a scientist too, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.01,0:11:47.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Then... you know how painful it would be\Nto lose your scientific work, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.56,0:11:50.52,Main,,0,0,0,,Do not compare me to Faraday!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.52,0:11:53.02,Main,,0,0,0,,He can't even do math!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.02,0:11:56.06,Main,,0,0,0,,He hasn't had a day's proper education!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.15,0:11:59.61,Main,,0,0,0,,He can't do anything
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.61,0:12:01.53,Main,,0,0,0,,except for running experiments over and over!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.53,0:12:03.53,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.53,0:12:04.57,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.57,0:12:07.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Getting results through constant experiments.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.24,0:12:09.41,Main,,0,0,0,,That's how he does science.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.41,0:12:12.08,Main,,0,0,0,,That's how he does the science he loves!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.08,0:12:14.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Losing yourself in something...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.21,0:12:17.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Losing yourself in just one thing...\NWhat's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.75,0:12:22.84,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with losing yourself\Nin what you love?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.06,0:12:33.73,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.15,0:12:40.94,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Faraday!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.50,0:12:54.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Where did he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.62,0:12:56.42,Main,,0,0,0,,How's it going, Shun?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.25,0:13:01.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, it says synchronization rate is 100%...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.30,0:13:03.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother? Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.80,0:13:08.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Is that you, Mari? Can you hear me? Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.26,0:13:10.76,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.76,0:13:12.27,Main,,0,0,0,,I can hear you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.27,0:13:14.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.56,0:13:17.31,Main,,0,0,0,,It's not on fast-forward anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.31,0:13:21.78,Main,,0,0,0,,I see! The armillary compass and\Nthe system have synchronized!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.78,0:13:24.11,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.11,0:13:26.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka! Listen close!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.07,0:13:29.12,Main,,0,0,0,,You know the knob\Nat the bottom of the compass?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.12,0:13:30.62,Main,,0,0,0,,Knob?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.66,0:13:32.58,Main,,0,0,0,,This?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.58,0:13:34.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.25,0:13:37.42,Main,,0,0,0,,If you turn that, you can come back here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.42,0:13:38.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.50,0:13:39.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.38,0:13:42.92,Main,,0,0,0,,That's how I got back from Mr. Volta's time!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.92,0:13:45.22,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.22,0:13:48.55,Main,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd never make it home!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.47,0:13:53.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, now. Don't cry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.39,0:13:56.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka, come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.19,0:13:58.52,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.11,0:14:04.48,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.48,0:14:09.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey... What's going to happen with\NMr. Faraday's discoveries and research?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.32,0:14:12.53,Main,,0,0,0,,To put it simply,\Nhis discovery will be the basis
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.53,0:14:15.00,Main,,0,0,0,,for the invention of the modern-day motor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.00,0:14:16.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Motor?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.46,0:14:21.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Then cars and washing machines and stuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.59,0:14:23.88,Main,,0,0,0,,We owe them all to Mr. Faraday?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.88,0:14:27.76,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes. His influence won't stop\Nat the scientific world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.76,0:14:31.76,Main,,0,0,0,,In a way, he's the man who laid\Nthe foundation for all modern culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.60,0:14:34.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.81,0:14:40.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Is it okay... if I stay here\Na little bit longer?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.95,0:14:53.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Where are you, Mr. Faraday?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.71,0:15:00.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Faraday!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.25,0:15:05.38,Main,,0,0,0,,I've been searching everywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.71,0:15:09.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you going to quit...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.09,0:15:10.68,Main,,0,0,0,,...quit science?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.68,0:15:15.43,Main,,0,0,0,,You can't quit. You can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.43,0:15:20.27,Main,,0,0,0,,What you're doing now will lead to some\Nvery important inventions in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.27,0:15:21.44,Main,,0,0,0,,In the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.44,0:15:23.02,Main,,0,0,0,,It's called a motor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.02,0:15:27.44,Main,,0,0,0,,You invent that, and it\Nimproves everybody's lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.44,0:15:32.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Motors have an incredible power...\Nthe power to move things!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.20,0:15:33.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.66,0:15:37.87,Main,,0,0,0,,You believe that science exists\Nto make people happy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.87,0:15:40.16,Main,,0,0,0,,You love science, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.16,0:15:42.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Then you can't stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.33,0:15:48.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Come on now, Waka. Who said\NI was going to give up on science?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.88,0:15:53.55,Main,,0,0,0,,What? But...\Nyou'd cleaned up all your things...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.55,0:15:57.35,Main,,0,0,0,,And you were here, staring off\Ninto the distance... so...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.35,0:15:59.02,Main,,0,0,0,,No, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.02,0:16:02.39,Main,,0,0,0,,I came up with a new experiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.39,0:16:06.15,Main,,0,0,0,,so I cleared off my desk\Nto make space for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.23,0:16:09.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Then why didn't you tell me that earlier?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.61,0:16:12.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Sorry! Anyway, let's get started!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.36,0:16:15.49,Main,,0,0,0,,If running electricity\Nthrough the copper wire
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.49,0:16:19.29,Main,,0,0,0,,can cause a magnet to rotate,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.29,0:16:21.83,Main,,0,0,0,,then thinking backwards from there,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.83,0:16:27.25,Main,,0,0,0,,you should be able to generate electricity\Nusing copper wire and magnets, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.59,0:16:30.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.34,0:16:31.92,Main,,0,0,0,,No reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.13,0:16:36.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's run some electricity through it,\Nto make sure the galvanometer is working.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.56,0:16:42.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Working normally.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.56,0:16:45.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's try it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.48,0:16:51.78,Main,,0,0,0,,No reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.78,0:16:53.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's change the direction of the magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.57,0:16:56.95,Main,,0,0,0,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.95,0:16:58.74,Main,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.74,0:17:00.79,Main,,0,0,0,,What about now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.37,0:17:03.96,Main,,0,0,0,,No reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.96,0:17:06.12,Main,,0,0,0,,No use, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.12,0:17:10.09,Main,,0,0,0,,It seems theoretically possible, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.09,0:17:15.34,Main,,0,0,0,,But not getting any result in an experiment\Nmakes it a failure, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.34,0:17:17.76,Main,,0,0,0,,A failure? That's no big deal!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.76,0:17:21.72,Main,,0,0,0,,That means I get to try\Nan all-new experiment!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.18,0:17:25.73,Main,,0,0,0,,What should I change for the next experiment?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.73,0:17:28.06,Main,,0,0,0,,What result will come from it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.06,0:17:30.44,Main,,0,0,0,,Just thinking about it gets me excited!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.44,0:17:33.99,Main,,0,0,0,,No matter how many times I fail,\Nno matter how hard it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.99,0:17:36.74,Main,,0,0,0,,I could never hate science!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.74,0:17:38.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Faraday...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.53,0:17:42.87,Main,,0,0,0,,So I'll never quit science, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.87,0:17:44.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.41,0:17:46.66,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.71,0:17:50.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Then I'll be going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.21,0:17:51.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.54,0:17:52.88,Main,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.67,0:17:56.30,Main,,0,0,0,,You found a way to get back, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.30,0:17:57.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.93,0:18:01.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Goodbye... Mr. Faraday.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.01,0:18:03.77,Main,,0,0,0,,Say hello to Mari. And your brother, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.77,0:18:05.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.06,0:18:11.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.48,0:18:17.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Waka.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.62,0:18:24.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.66,0:18:25.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.45,0:18:27.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.33,0:18:30.13,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad! I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.13,0:18:32.29,Main,,0,0,0,,So, so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.29,0:18:34.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.46,0:18:35.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.67,0:18:37.34,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.34,0:18:39.80,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry I worried you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.80,0:18:41.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Did you do what you had to?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.85,0:18:43.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.89,0:18:49.73,Main,,0,0,0,,After conducting the electromagnetic\Nrotation experiment in 1821,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.73,0:18:54.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Faraday continued exploring the relationship\Nbetween magnetism and electricity
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.23,0:18:58.86,Main,,0,0,0,,until 1831, when an experiment led him\Nto discover the Law of Induction,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.86,0:19:02.41,Main,,0,0,0,,which would later be\Nknown as Faraday's Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.41,0:19:06.20,Main,,0,0,0,,The faster the lines\Nof magnetic force change,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.20,0:19:09.37,Main,,0,0,0,,and the more coils in the circuit,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.37,0:19:12.46,Main,,0,0,0,,the greater their induced current becomes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.46,0:19:17.38,Main,,0,0,0,,That law became indispensable in\Nlater thinking about generating electricity,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.38,0:19:20.43,Main,,0,0,0,,and became the cornerstone\Nof the study of electromagnetism.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.43,0:19:22.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? This book...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.39,0:19:23.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.97,0:19:28.85,Main,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.85,0:19:30.14,Main,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.14,0:19:31.35,Main,,0,0,0,,It didn't disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.35,0:19:32.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.52,0:19:36.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Morse. Bell.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.07,0:19:37.90,Main,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.90,0:19:41.03,Main,,0,0,0,,Hertz. Edison.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.03,0:19:43.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Is it because we're\Nin control of the machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.24,0:19:48.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Or because our power source has switched\Nfrom a battery to a standard outlet?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.54,0:19:55.96,Main,,0,0,0,,I will not acknowledge it. I won't!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.96,0:19:59.34,Main,,0,0,0,,I will not acknowledge Faraday's assertion!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.34,0:20:03.09,Main,,0,0,0,,I'd advise you to stop, Sir Davy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.18,0:20:07.39,Main,,0,0,0,,Is there something else you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.39,0:20:12.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Faraday will make enormous contributions\Nto the scientific world in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.27,0:20:13.98,Main,,0,0,0,,And, Sir Davy,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.98,0:20:18.94,Main,,0,0,0,,your greatest contribution\Nwill be discovering him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.74,0:20:23.61,Main,,0,0,0,,You realize that, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.41,0:20:34.37,Main,,0,0,0,,"Intermediate English\NProblems by Level"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.29,0:20:37.79,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.34,0:20:39.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Wh-What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.96,0:20:43.76,Main,,0,0,0,,This isn't for club! I'm just taking a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.76,0:20:46.43,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm studying properly, I tell you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.43,0:20:47.55,Main,,0,0,0,,It's upside-down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.47,0:20:50.22,Main,,0,0,0,,I... I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.22,0:20:54.52,Main,,0,0,0,,You won't accomplish anything by doing\Nsuch a half-baked job on everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.52,0:20:55.77,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.77,0:20:58.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Next week is your match, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.48,0:21:01.11,Main,,0,0,0,,I got them to give you\Npermission to practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.11,0:21:01.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.86,0:21:05.41,Main,,0,0,0,,But you have to get\N80% or more on the next test.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.41,0:21:07.20,Main,,0,0,0,,That's the condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.20,0:21:09.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Where did this come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.16,0:21:12.91,Main,,0,0,0,,After practice, I'll teach you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.91,0:21:15.87,Main,,0,0,0,,So get going, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.08,0:21:19.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Futa.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.04,0:21:20.67,Main,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.67,0:21:24.76,Main,,0,0,0,,You're really good at soccer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.76,0:21:28.18,Main,,0,0,0,,And... you love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.18,0:21:31.56,Main,,0,0,0,,So... you should aim\Nfor the top... or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.56,0:21:32.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.56,0:21:34.52,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.52,0:21:37.90,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you to work hard at soccer!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.81,0:21:41.61,Main,,0,0,0,,You know I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.61,0:21:44.57,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm going to the World Cup, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.57,0:21:47.45,Main,,0,0,0,,And if I need it to get there...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.45,0:21:51.45,Main,,0,0,0,,...I've gotta work hard at studying,\Ntoo, even if I don't like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.45,0:21:55.04,Main,,0,0,0,,I know you'll make it, Futa.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.04,0:21:56.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.21,0:21:58.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Mizuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.55,0:22:08.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mikage.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.93,0:22:13.39,Main,,0,0,0,,You have a call from Mr. Sekota,\Nthe research assistant you met with before.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.39,0:22:14.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.85,0:22:18.60,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes? Mikage speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.02,0:22:21.77,Main,,0,0,0,,You remembered something?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.40,0:22:25.69,Main,,0,0,0,,A book?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.69,0:22:27.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Magnets and Electricity...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.45,0:22:29.86,Main,,0,0,0,,"Next Episode: Morse's Inspiration"\NMagnets and Electricity...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.95,0:24:00.46,Main,,0,0,0,,"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.46,0:24:02.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari and Waka's Quick Science!\N"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.04,0:24:07.00,Main,,0,0,0,,What was Mr. Faraday trying to accomplish?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.00,0:24:12.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Last time, he learned that changes in current\Nand magnetic field produce power, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.13,0:24:13.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.09,0:24:14.64,Main,,0,0,0,,He was testing the opposite of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.64,0:24:18.97,Main,,0,0,0,,That the movement of a magnet\Ncould generate electric current.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.97,0:24:22.44,Main,,0,0,0,,But it didn't work...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.44,0:24:27.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Later, he learned that by coiling copper wire\Nand running a magnet through it...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.32,0:24:29.23,Main,,0,0,0,,It worked!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.23,0:24:30.65,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's test it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.65,0:24:33.03,Main,,0,0,0,,Wrap a coil around an acrylic tube,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.03,0:24:35.74,Main,,0,0,0,,pass a magnet through, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.28,0:24:39.99,Main,,0,0,0,,The needle moved!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.37,0:24:40.70,Main,,0,0,0,,"Structure of a Generator"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.70,0:24:43.54,Main,,0,0,0,,The truth is, when the magnet\Ngets close to the coil,\N"Structure of a Generator"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.54,0:24:47.00,Main,,0,0,0,,it changes the magnetic field inside the coil\Nand causes electricity to flow.\N"Structure of a Generator"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.00,0:24:50.46,Main,,0,0,0,,This principle became\Nthe basis for the generator.\N"Structure of a Generator"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.46,0:24:51.13,Main,,0,0,0,,This principle became\Nthe basis for the generator.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.13,0:24:56.09,Main,,0,0,0,,When we rotate the handle of this\Nhand-cranked generator, attached to an LED...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.09,0:24:57.39,Main,,0,0,0,,So bright!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.39,0:24:58.76,Main,,0,0,0,,\N\NIt turned on!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.76,0:24:59.68,Main,,0,0,0,,"Electric Current" "Power" "Magnetic Field"\N\NIt turned on!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.68,0:25:03.94,Main,,0,0,0,,"Electric Current" "Power" "Magnetic Field"\NThere's a coil and a magnet\Ninside the generator.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.94,0:25:06.77,Main,,0,0,0,,"Electric Current" "Power" "Magnetic Field"\N\NHuh? That looks like a motor.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.77,0:25:07.36,Main,,0,0,0,,\N\NHuh? That looks like a motor.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.36,0:25:11.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Now, when we swap the LED for a battery...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.19,0:25:14.45,Main,,0,0,0,,The handle turned!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.45,0:25:18.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Which means the system is the same,\Nbut the principle is reversed?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.45,0:25:20.08,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.08,0:25:22.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Faraday invented the basic\Nprinciple behind the motor,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.79,0:25:26.50,Main,,0,0,0,,and from there, he arrived at\Nthe principle behind the generator.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.50,0:25:29.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Thinking backwards\Nreally can advance science, huh?
